-- Generated by scripts/generate-pops-seed.js from Assets/Data/Privately_Owned_Public_Spaces.csv
-- and the 3 pilot GeoJSON polygons. Do not hand-edit; re-run the generator instead.
-- id is a deterministic uuid derived from each space's POPS_Number (pilots: from their scan
-- slug), so re-running this script and re-running these inserts is always safe (on conflict
-- do nothing) — nothing is ever duplicated, and nothing here ever deletes existing rows.

-- The 3 real pilot spaces (status = active), lat/lng are their GeoJSON polygon centroids.
-- scan_slug links each to its 3d-space/?scan=<slug> page. noise is simulated (see header
-- comment in generate-pops-seed.js) — no sensor hardware exists for this pilot.
on conflict (id) do nothing;

-- The 389 real NYC POPS from the official dataset, shown but not yet active. noise is
-- simulated the same way as the pilots' — see generate-pops-seed.js header comment.
on conflict (id) do nothing;
